**
terraform commands

terraform init = This command is use to add or download necessary files

terraform plan = to check for errors

terraform apply = to apply the changes to platform

terraform destroy = to destroy all the modules in the code

terraform destroy target name_of_target = this is use to destroy or delete a specific module in code 

terraform refresh = This command checks the letest state of your infrastructure and update stage file accordingly.

terraform fmt = set the format of the code in easy readable manner

terraform validate = validate command is primarily check the file syntax are valid or not 

terraform output resource_name - this command show you the output of resources

terraform plan -refresh=flase -target=resource_name.local_name = Stop the refreshing processos in treeaform command and only plan for specific resource

